  14,34,"And He gave you from all that you asked Him. And if you count Godâ€™s favor, you cannot count it. The human being is certainly wrongdoer and ungrateful"
  14,35,"And remember when Abraham said: my Master, make this territory safe, and keep me and my children away from serving idols"
  14,36,"My Master, indeed they misguided a lot of people, so whoever follows me then he is of me, and whoever disobeys me, indeed You are forgiving and merciful"
  14,37,"Our Master, indeed I made some of my descendants live in a barren valley by Your sacred house, so that they may perform the mandatory prayer our Master, so make hearts of the people fond of them, and provide them with the produce so they may be thankful"
  14,38,"Our Master, you know what we hide and what we disclose, and nothing in the skies and in the earth hides from God"
  14,39,"All praise belongs to God, the One who gave me Ishmael and Isaac in spite of the old age. Indeed my Master is the listener of the prayer"
  14,40,"My Master, make me and my descendants performers of the mandatory prayer, and accept my prayer our Master"
  14,41,"Our Master, forgive me and my parents and the believers on a day that the accounting is established"
  14,42,And do not think that God is unaware of what the wrongdoers do. God only postpones them (their punishment) to a day that the eyes stare (in horror) in it